    {
        "content": "<p>Are there any plans to add a subcommand to quickly start a new Roc project? Something like <code>cargo new</code>.</p>\n<p>Would probably want to be able to create a new package and specify the name, defaulting to the name of the directory if none is given which is what <code>cargo new</code> does.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>roc<span class=\"w\"> </span>new<span class=\"w\"> </span>package<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span>--name<span class=\"o\">=</span>my-package<span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>.\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>And also create an app with a given platform:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>roc<span class=\"w\"> </span>new<span class=\"w\"> </span>app<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span>--name<span class=\"o\">=</span>my-app<span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span>--platform<span class=\"o\">=</span>https://...<span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>.\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 373978035,
        "sender_full_name": "Hannes",
        "timestamp": 1688998561
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Would probably also want to borrow a bunch of <code>cargo new</code>'s arguments like <code>--vcs=git</code> or <code>--git</code> for initialising a git repo, etc.</p>",
        "id": 373978730,
        "sender_full_name": "Hannes",
        "timestamp": 1688998685
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Richard proposed <code>roc init</code> last year: <a href=\"https://github.com/roc-lang/roc/issues/3139\">#3139</a></p>",
        "id": 373988369,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1689000567
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, thank you! It felt like something that would've been mentioned somewhere :)</p>",
